g.text: Rhetoric: I can talk you out of it, whatever it is.
Suggestion: You're too likable to die. Don't worry.
Hand/Eye Coordination: You are prepared. Don't put away your friend. Your weapon.
Interfacing: Snowflakes speck the barrels of your Nachtwey A80 pistol.
Inland Empire: Stop. Just up ahead: danger.
Inland Empire: Good. Be ready to take damage.
You: "I'm not sure I feel ready for what lies ahead."
Physical Instrument: Snowflakes stick to your prybar. Or crowbar. Or prybar. Call it what you will -- it doesn't stand a chance against military-grade weaponry.
Inland Empire: Stop. Now. It is time.
Inland Empire: Your old friend has prepared you for this -- at great cost to himself. Make sure you have the spirit bomb in your hand when *shit goes south*.
Inland Empire: You are prepared. Don't put away your friend. Your weapon. It is glowing in your hand, ready to serve.
Composure: The oily tail end of your necktie-turned-fuse glistens in the cool spring light.
Physical Instrument: Water streams down your prybar. Or crowbar. Or prybar. Call it what you will -- it doesn't stand a chance against military-grade weaponry.
Physical Instrument: You try to take comfort in the weight of your prybar. Or crowbar. Or prybar. Call it what you will -- it doesn't stand a chance against military-grade weaponry.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Then you'd better get ready." He frowns, then quickly adds, "Whatever happens, I've got your back."
Perception (Hearing): You hear what sounds like an enthusiastic gurgling coming from the spirit bomb in your pocket.
Inland Empire: Stop. Just up ahead: danger.
Authority: What?! You can't compare the sidearm issued to you personally by the RCM to the pistol of a known criminal?
Inland Empire: Yes. And it's not going to be fun.
Inland Empire: Arm yourself with anything you can. Unless you have... nothing? Because you didn't find your lost gun? Then just walk to your death.
Hand/Eye Coordination: You are prepared. Don't put away your friend. Your weapon.
Inland Empire: Crisis, death. You can feel it in your blue soul.
Composure: Snow gathers on the oily fabric of the tail end of your necktie-turned-fuse.
You: I'm ready to do this.
Interfacing: Your Kvalsund KR+2 Multi-Tool looks impressive, shining in the cold spring light -- but what can it do against military-grade weaponry?
Inland Empire: Wait -- your old friend has prepared you for this -- at great cost to himself. Make sure you have the spirit bomb in your hand when *shit goes south*.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. I hear commotion..." He cups his ear. "Let's go."
Interfacing: Snowflakes speck the barrels of your Villiers 9mm pistol.
You: I'll feel prepared as soon as I switch out my real police gun.
Logic: There really isn't much of a difference between these two guns...
Inland Empire: This is not the time to discuss preferences. It's not just your own life that will be at stake.
And you think you're off to die an honourable death? What about the lives of the people depending on you?
Interfacing: Snowflakes stick to your Kvalsund KR+2 Multi-Tool. It looks impressive -- but what can it do against military-grade weaponry?
Interfacing: Raindrops slip from the barrels of your Villiers 9mm pistol.
Inland Empire: No, no. You cannot get off that easy. This is serious. Lives are at stake.
Inland Empire: It would be better if you didn't have to. It's not just your own life that will be at stake.
Interfacing: Your fingers reflexively reach for the Villiers 9mm pistol in your pocket.
Inland Empire: Be prepared. Wield Ruby's double-barrelled pistol.
Inland Empire: Shush. He's not drinking the spirit bomb. He's putting it in his hand and he's going to be ready.
Encyclopedia: Statistically speaking, sabres have proven to be rather ineffective against advanced military technology.
Composure: Raindrops slip down the oily fabric of the tail end of your necktie-turned-fuse.
Inland Empire: Do what you need to do. And then keep moving toward the future.
"I prefer hand-to-hand combat. It's more honourable."
Inland Empire: This isn't the time for fear. Go.
Electrochemistry: You know what you should do? Take out the spirit bomb...
You: I'll fight with my bare hands if I have to.
You: What am I supposed to do?
Authority: What a shitty gun. But it's better than nothing.
Inland Empire: Stop. Just up ahead: danger.
